A good place to start when looking for higher-order component typings is other packages or `@types` packages.

- [`react-i18next`](https://github.com/i18next/react-i18next/blob/94916045c2a5c72bef9691b94fef04fcfcdbe733/src/index.d.ts#L63-L75)
- [`react-redux`](https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/blob/d0cd7f859d0eb5b690ea1714ef197da819b14f99/types/react-redux/index.d.ts#L173-L286) _(these are complex)_
- [`react-router-dom`](https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/blob/d0cd7f859d0eb5b690ea1714ef197da819b14f99/types/react-router/index.d.ts#L146-L148)

However, your use case is a bit interesting because you want the wrapped component to receive more props and each wrapping higher-order component provides one of these values.

Given that, here is one potential solution. A few things to point out:

- Assuming you want to allow any component type (class or function), reaching for the [`React.ComponentType`](https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped/blob/d0cd7f859d0eb5b690ea1714ef197da819b14f99/types/react/index.d.ts#L71) is probably what you want.
- I try to avoid casts but it looks like this is still a shortcoming (issue) with TypeScript. These two issues looked relevant: [#28884](https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/issues/28884) &amp; [#28748](https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/issues/28748)
- `Omit` is added for reference because before it doesn&#39;t exist before `3.5` (I was testing in Codesandbox which at this time is still at `3.3`)

```typescript
import * as React from &quot;react&quot;;
import { render } from &quot;react-dom&quot;;

// This exists in TypeScript 3.5+
type Omit&lt;T, K extends keyof T&gt; = Pick&lt;T, Exclude&lt;keyof T, K&gt;&gt;;

interface FooProps {
  foo: string;
}

interface BarProps {
  bar: string;
}

export const withFoo = &lt;Props extends FooProps&gt;(
  Component: React.ComponentType&lt;Props&gt;
): React.ComponentType&lt;Omit&lt;Props, keyof FooProps&gt;&gt; =&gt; props =&gt; (
  &lt;Component {...props as Props} foo=&quot;foo&quot; /&gt;
);

export const withBar = &lt;Props extends BarProps&gt;(
  Component: React.ComponentType&lt;Props&gt;
): React.ComponentType&lt;Omit&lt;Props, keyof BarProps&gt;&gt; =&gt; props =&gt; (
  &lt;Component {...props as Props} bar=&quot;bar&quot; /&gt;
);

const WrappedComponent = ({ bar, foo, more }) =&gt; {
  console.log(more);
  console.log(bar);
  console.log(foo);
  return &lt;div&gt;woohoo&lt;/div&gt;;
};

const EnhancedComponent = withFoo(withBar(WrappedComponent));

const App = () =&gt; &lt;EnhancedComponent more=&quot;more&quot; /&gt;;

const rootElement = document.getElementById(&quot;root&quot;);
render(&lt;App /&gt;, rootElement);
```

